Multi-language code query tool using XPath 3.1

Usage: tractor [OPTIONS] [FILES]...
       tractor <COMMAND>

Commands:
  query   Query source code ASTs with XPath (default when no subcommand given)
  check   Run checks and report violations (lint mode)
  test    Test expectations against match counts
  set     Set matched node values (modify files in-place, create missing nodes)
  update  Update matched node values (modify files in-place, skip if not found)
  render  [EXPERIMENTAL] Render XML AST back to source code
  run     Execute a tractor config file (batch check/set operations)
  init    Create a starter tractor.yml in the current directory
  docs    Show documentation and reference information
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Arguments:
  [FILES]...  Files to process (supports glob patterns like "src/**/*.cs")

Options:
  -l, --lang <LANG>       Language for stdin or -s/--string input (e.g., csharp, rust, python)
  -s, --string <CONTENT>  Source code string to parse (alternative to stdin, requires --lang)
  -h, --help              Print help (see more with '--help')

Config:
      --config <CONFIG>  Path to a tractor config file (YAML/TOML) — runs only query operations from it

Extract:
  -x, --extract <QUERY>    XPath expression to extract matching AST nodes
  -t, --tree <TREE>        Tree mode: raw, structure, data [default: auto]
  -W, --ignore-whitespace  Ignore whitespace in XPath string matching (strips whitespace from text nodes)

View:
  -n, --limit <LIMIT>        Limit output to first N matches
  -p, --projection <TARGET>  Select a specific report projection (tree, summary, results, report, ...)
      --single               Emit only the first projected item, bare with no list wrapper
  -d, --depth <DEPTH>        Limit XML output depth (useful for large ASTs)
      --meta                 Include metadata attributes (start/end, kind, field) in XML output
  -g, --group <GROUP_BY>     Group output by dimension: none, file, command, rule (comma-separated)
  -v, --view <VIEW>          Report fields to include (e.g. tree, value, source) [default: file,line,tree]
  -m, --message <MESSAGE>    Custom message template (supports {value}, {line}, {col}, {file})

Format:
      --no-pretty        Disable pretty printing (shows XML without formatting, as used by XPath)
      --color <COLOR>    Color output: auto (default), always, never [default: auto]
      --no-color         Disable color output
      --hook <HOOK>      Claude Code hook type (used with -f claude-code): post-tool-use, pre-tool-use, stop, context
  -f, --format <FORMAT>  Output format [default: text] [default: text]

Filter:
      --diff-files <RANGE>  Only consider files changed in a git diff (e.g. "HEAD~3", "main..HEAD")
      --diff-lines <RANGE>  Only consider matches in changed hunks of a git diff (e.g. "HEAD~3", "main..HEAD")

Advanced:
      --parse-depth <PARSE_DEPTH>  [EXPERIMENTAL] Limit tree building depth (skip parsing deeper nodes for speed)
  -c, --concurrency <CONCURRENCY>  Number of parallel workers
      --max-files <MAX_FILES>      Maximum number of files to process (default: 10000) [default: 10000]
      --verbose                    Show verbose output
      --debug                      Show full XML with matches highlighted (for debugging XPath)
  -V, --version                    Print version information (use with --verbose for detailed output)

